p: \bWhat's poppin' little Machop... in?\nNever mind.\nWelcome to the Vipik City Gym!
\bThe Leader here, Xavier, runs a Forest-themed Gym.
\bThat's right! This Gym is dual-typed! It's based around a theme, and not a type!
\bBug- and Poison-types are the name of the game!
\bWhenever you're ready, just climb into the hole in the tree.
\bThis Gym is a maze of tree-holes!
\bNicely done, champ, I can't believe you beat Xavier!\nYour next target, I assume, is East in Helios City.\nYou might want to bring an Ice-type, you'll see why!

\bI train Pokemon as a profession. I'm the Leader here.
\bI'll take you on whenever you're ready!\nI'm not as much of a pushover as I look!
\bPlus...\n...I have a little surprise up my sleeve!\nLet's get started!
\bI'm so glad we got to have a battle, though.
\bI had a ton of fun! It's with great pride I award you my badge!
\bHow did you like my Beedrill, though?
\bThat's called Mega Evolution! It's pretty impressive, right?
\bMaybe one day you'll get to do it too...
\bTake this too. A gift from me!
\bVenoshock is usually a pretty mediocre move.\nIt only has 65 power.
\bBut if it's used on a Pokemon that's been poisoned, it doubles in power!
\bI think you'll want to head out to Helios City for your next Gym.\nThe Leader there has a gym based around the sky!
\bYou beat me fair and square!\nGreat work!
Battle: \bI'm glad I wasn't stationed near Xavier's room.\nThere's always this weird mist in there that makes me feel odd.
EndSpeech: Not sure if it's legal, but whatever.
